        "content": "<p>alexcrichton opened <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13558\">PR #13558</a> from <code>alexcrichton:remove-wasi-threads-and-common</code> to <code>bytecodealliance:main</code>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>For more context and rationale, see<br>\n<a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/rfcs/pull/47\">https://github.com/bytecodealliance/rfcs/pull/47</a>. With <code>main</code> now as the Wasmtime 47.0.0 branch this commit deletes this support from <code>main</code>. Note that Wasmtime 46.0.0 will be the last version with support, and Wasmtime 36.0.0, which has support, will continue to be supported by the project for another year.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: wasmtime 46 doesn't actually branch until tomorrow, but I wanted to pump this through CI</p>\n</blockquote>\n</blockquote>",
